Human-readable summary:

  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

License rationale (per datasheet.md):

  CC-BY-4.0 was chosen because (a) the dataset includes verbatim drafts
  from the Tenacious Style Guide v2, which we want to be reusable for
  research and education; (b) attribution preserves provenance traceback
  to Tenacious's documented voice and the 10Academy TRP1 program; and
  (c) commercial use is permitted because the benchmark is intended to
  be deployable in production B2B sales evaluation pipelines.

  No real prospect data is included. All synthetic prospect names
  ("Maya", "Daniel", "Priya", etc.) are fictitious; any resemblance to
  actual companies or persons is coincidental.

